    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 3300: Minimum Element After Replacement With Digit Sum (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array nums. You can replace each element of the array with the sum of its
                digits. Perform this operation until all elements in the array are single digits. Return the minimum
                element in the final array.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [10,12,13,14]<br>
                Output: 1<br>
                Explanation: Replace 10 with 1+0=1, replace 12 with 1+2=3, replace 13 with 1+3=4, replace 14 with 1+4=5.
                The array becomes [1,3,4,5]. The minimum is 1.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minElement(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int ans = INT_MAX;
        for (int val : nums) {
            int sum = 0;
            // Extract and add digits
            while (val) {
                sum += val % 10;
                val /= 10;
            }
            ans = min(ans, sum);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};</code></pre>
